{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1773435856081,"sessionID":"ses_316fcc12bffeSBLLi3jBrbT2M4","part":{"id":"prt_ce903a4d00017gXTuFYp3siNWN","sessionID":"ses_316fcc12bffeSBLLi3jBrbT2M4","messageID":"msg_ce9039950001OZDwcfWLOihb9i","type":"step-start","snapshot":"71a9ece88ba5cd3af81058dbf99f461438ca0ed5"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1773435895243,"sessionID":"ses_316fcc12bffeSBLLi3jBrbT2M4","part":{"id":"prt_ce903a4d1001m3AZZLoyThYCpK","sessionID":"ses_316fcc12bffeSBLLi3jBrbT2M4","messageID":"msg_ce9039950001OZDwcfWLOihb9i","type":"text","text":"## Goal\n\nImplement a comprehensive unit test suite for the wombo-combo project using Bun's built-in test runner (`bun test`). This is a critical task created after a bug that destroyed the project root (a `.includes()` vs `.startsWith()` issue in worktree filtering). The umbrella task covers 4 sub-areas: task YAML parsing/validation, state management, worktree filtering, duration parsing, dependency resolution, CLI arg parsing, and task schema validation.\n\n## Instructions\n\n- Use **only** Bun's built-in test runner (`bun test`) — no jest, vitest, or external test frameworks\n- Must cover worktree filtering edge cases (basename vs full-path matching — the bug that rm -rf'd the project)\n- Must cover arg parsing edge cases (trailing flags, missing values)\n- Must cover task YAML parsing (null, empty, invalid schema, invalid enums)\n- Use conventional commits: `feat(scope):`, `fix(scope):`, `refactor(scope):`, `docs(scope):`\n- Commit after each logical unit of work (roughly per subtask)\n- Do NOT push to remote — the orchestrator handles that\n- After completing all changes, run `bun run build` to verify everything works\n- The branch is `feature/unit-test-suite`, base is `main`\n\n## Discoveries\n\n1. **Tests already exist!** There are 5 test files already in `tests/`:\n   - `tests/arg-parsing.test.ts` — Very comprehensive (1292 lines), covers basic commands, aliases, flags, trailing flags via subprocess, unknown flags, positional args, real-world examples\n   - `tests/features.test.ts` — Comprehensive (873 lines), covers duration parsing, formatting, loadFeatures YAML edge cases, dependency resolution, selection strategies, createBlankFeature, findFeatureById, priority/difficulty ordering\n   - `tests/state.test.ts` — Comprehensive (643 lines), covers generateWaveId, createWaveState, createAgentState, save/load round-trip, atomic writes, corruption recovery, updateAgent, agentCounts, activeAgents, queuedAgents, isWaveComplete, concurrent mutations\n   - `tests/worktree.test.ts` — Unit-level tests (484 lines), covers featureBranchName, worktreePath, basename filtering logic (both correct and buggy versions), removeWorktree safety guard, porcelain output parsing\n   - `tests/worktree-filtering.test.ts` — Integration tests (850 lines) using real temporary git repos, covers listWomboWorktrees, removeWorktree safety, cleanupAllWorktrees, verifyConfigFiles, createWorktree config file copying, prefix substring edge cases\n\n2. **The task store uses folder-based storage now** — tasks are stored as individual YAML files in `.wombo-combo/tasks/` and `.wombo-combo/archive/` directories, with `_meta.yml` for metadata. The `loadFeatures()` function delegates to `loadTasksFromStore()` in `task-store.ts`.\n\n3. **The `features.test.ts` uses legacy single-file approach** (`writeTasksYaml` writing to `.wombo-combo/tasks.yml`) which should trigger the auto-migration path in `task-store.ts`. This is intentional for backward compat testing.\n\n4. **The config type (`WomboConfig`) has `tdd` and `agentRegistry.cacheTTL` fields** that the test helper `makeConfig()` functions in existing tests may not include — this could cause type errors.\n\n5. **tsconfig.json only includes `src/**/*.ts`** — tests directory is excluded from TypeScript compilation, which is fine for `bun test` since Bun handles TypeScript natively.\n\n6. **Key source modules** that are being tested: `src/lib/tasks.ts`, `src/lib/state.ts`, `src/lib/worktree.ts`, `src/index.ts` (parseArgs), `src/lib/task-schema.ts`, `src/lib/task-store.ts`, `src/lib/validate.ts`, `src/config.ts`.\n\n## Accomplished\n\n- **Read and analyzed all relevant source files** — understood the codebase structure, types, and module interfaces\n- **Read all 5 existing test files** — they appear to already be comprehensive and cover all the required areas from the task description\n- **No changes have been made yet** — no files created/modified, no commits made, no build verification run\n\n## What needs to be done next\n\n1. **Run the existing tests** with `bun test` to see if they pass\n2. **Identify gaps** — check if existing tests fully cover the constraints:\n   - Task YAML parsing with null, empty, invalid schema, invalid enums ✓ (in features.test.ts)\n   - Worktree filtering edge cases (basename vs full-path) ✓ (in worktree.test.ts and worktree-filtering.test.ts)\n   - Arg parsing edge cases (trailing flags, missing values) ✓ (in arg-parsing.test.ts)\n3. **Add missing test coverage** if any gaps are found — particularly:\n   - `task-schema.ts` validation (validateTask, validateMeta with invalid enums, missing fields)\n   - `validate.ts` input validators (validateId, validateText, validateBranchName, validateDuration)\n   - `config.ts` (loadConfig, validateConfig, deepMerge)\n   - Dependency-aware state helpers (areAgentDepsReady, readyToLaunchAgents, getDownstreamAgents, cancelDownstream)\n4. **Fix any type errors** in makeConfig helpers (missing `tdd` and `agentRegistry.cacheTTL`)\n5. **Add a test script** to package.json if not present\n6. **Run `bun run build`** to verify everything works\n7. **Commit changes** with conventional commit messages\n\n## Relevant files / directories\n\n### Source files being tested\n- `src/index.ts` — CLI entry point, parseArgs, COMMAND_ALIASES, SUBCOMMAND_ALIASES\n- `src/config.ts` — WomboConfig type, loadConfig, validateConfig, DEFAULT_CONFIG, deepMerge\n- `src/lib/tasks.ts` — Task types, parseDurationMinutes, formatDuration, dependency resolution, selection strategies\n- `src/lib/state.ts` — WaveState, AgentState, save/load state, agent mutations, dependency-aware helpers\n- `src/lib/worktree.ts` — Worktree management, listWomboWorktrees, removeWorktree safety guard, basename filtering\n- `src/lib/task-schema.ts` — VALID_STATUSES/PRIORITIES/DIFFICULTIES, validateTask, validateMeta\n- `src/lib/task-store.ts` — Folder-based task storage, normalizeTask, migration logic\n- `src/lib/validate.ts` — Input validation (validateId, validateText, validateBranchName, validateDuration)\n- `src/lib/output.ts` — resolveOutputFormat, filterFields\n\n### Existing test files\n- `tests/arg-parsing.test.ts`\n- `tests/features.test.ts`\n- `tests/state.test.ts`\n- `tests/worktree.test.ts`\n- `tests/worktree-filtering.test.ts`\n\n### Config files\n- `package.json` — scripts, dependencies (no \"test\" script currently)\n- `tsconfig.json` — excludes tests/ from compilation\n- `AGENTS.md` — coding conventions and constraints","time":{"start":1773435895241,"end":1773435895241}}}
