{"type":"text","timestamp":1773435989363,"sessionID":"ses_316fcc12bffeSBLLi3jBrbT2M4","part":{"id":"prt_ce9057c410016625XM0ehY422V","sessionID":"ses_316fcc12bffeSBLLi3jBrbT2M4","messageID":"msg_ce90575c6001r2RQsHhXjRYsVl","type":"text","text":"Now I understand all three issues clearly. Let me fix them:\n\n**Failure 1**: \"handles nested subtasks normalization\" - With folder-based migration, subtasks are flattened to top-level tasks. The test should verify the flattened form instead.\n\n**Failure 2**: \"throws on corrupted YAML\" - `loadTasksFromStore` → `migrateTasksIfNeeded` catches parse errors and returns `false`, then the store returns an empty `TasksFile`. It no longer throws.\n\n**Failure 3**: \"throws on missing file\" - Same: `loadTasksFromStore` returns empty `TasksFile` instead of throwing.","time":{"start":1773435989362,"end":1773435989362}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773435989932,"sessionID":"ses_316fcc12bffeSBLLi3jBrbT2M4","part":{"id":"prt_ce9058af9001blgCNBxiPsaIqv","sessionID":"ses_316fcc12bffeSBLLi3jBrbT2M4","messageID":"msg_ce90575c6001r2RQsHhXjRYsVl","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01TxqRuu3gAsrWvcefuHTMa7","tool":"edit","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wt-wombo-unit-test-suite/tests/features.test.ts","oldString":"  test(\"handles nested subtasks normalization\", () => {\n    const yaml = `\nversion: \"1\"\nmeta:\n  created_at: \"2025-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n  updated_at: \"2025-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n  project: test\n  generator: test\n  maintainer: tester\ntasks:\n  - id: feat-a\n    title: Feature A\n    description: \"\"\n    status: backlog\n    completion: 0\n    difficulty: medium\n    priority: medium\n    effort: PT1H\n    started_at: null\n    ended_at: null\n    subtasks:\n      - id: sub-1\n        title: Subtask 1\n        description: \"\"\n        status: backlog\n        completion: 0\n        difficulty: easy\n        priority: medium\n        effort: PT30M\n        started_at: null\n        ended_at: null\n`;\n    writeTasksYaml(tmpDir, yaml);\n    const data = loadFeatures(tmpDir, config);\n    const subtask = data.tasks[0].subtasks[0];\n    expect(subtask.id).toBe(\"sub-1\");\n    expect(subtask.depends_on).toBeArray();\n    expect(subtask.constraints).toBeArray();\n    expect(subtask.subtasks).toBeArray();\n  });","newString":"  test(\"handles nested subtasks normalization (flattened by migration)\", () => {\n    // With folder-based storage, subtasks are flattened to top-level tasks\n    // during migration. The parent task gains a depends_on reference to its\n    // former subtask, and the subtask becomes a standalone top-level task.\n    const yaml = `\nversion: \"1\"\nmeta:\n  created_at: \"2025-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n  updated_at: \"2025-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n  project: test\n  generator: test\n  maintainer: tester\ntasks:\n  - id: feat-a\n    title: Feature A\n    description: \"\"\n    status: backlog\n    completion: 0\n    difficulty: medium\n    priority: medium\n    effort: PT1H\n    started_at: null\n    ended_at: null\n    subtasks:\n      - id: sub-1\n        title: Subtask 1\n        description: \"\"\n        status: backlog\n        completion: 0\n        difficulty: easy\n        priority: medium\n        effort: PT30M\n        started_at: null\n        ended_at: null\n`;\n    writeTasksYaml(tmpDir, yaml);\n    const data = loadFeatures(tmpDir, config);\n    // After migration, both feat-a and sub-1 are top-level tasks\n    const ids = data.tasks.map((t) => t.id).sort();\n    expect(ids).toContain(\"feat-a\");\n    expect(ids).toContain(\"sub-1\");\n    // The parent's subtasks array is empty (flattened)\n    const parent = data.tasks.find((t) => t.id === \"feat-a\")!;\n    expect(parent.subtasks).toBeArray();\n    expect(parent.subtasks).toHaveLength(0);\n    // The parent now depends on its former subtask\n    expect(parent.depends_on).toContain(\"sub-1\");\n    // The former subtask is a top-level task with normalized arrays\n    const subtask = data.tasks.find((t) => t.id === \"sub-1\")!;\n    expect(subtask.depends_on).toBeArray();\n    expect(subtask.constraints).toBeArray();\n    expect(subtask.subtasks).toBeArray();\n  });"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in this file, please fix:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wt-wombo-unit-test-suite/tests/features.test.ts\">\nERROR [86:5] Property 'cacheTTL' is missing in type '{ mode: \"auto\"; source: string; cacheDir: string; }' but required in type 'AgentRegistryConfig'.\n</diagnostics>","title":"tests/features.test.ts","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wt-wombo-unit-test-suite/src/lib/worktree.ts":[],"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wt-wombo-unit-test-suite/src/index.ts":[{"range":{"start":{"line":585,"character":10},"end":{"line":585,"character":16}},"message":"Unreachable code 