{"type":"text","timestamp":1773436448225,"sessionID":"ses_316fcc12bffeSBLLi3jBrbT2M4","part":{"id":"prt_ce90bde85001LEQsxdRUxQDbdg","sessionID":"ses_316fcc12bffeSBLLi3jBrbT2M4","messageID":"msg_ce90bd395001ar2MHslVGbuPWe","type":"text","text":"## Goal\n\nImplement a comprehensive unit test suite for the wombo-combo project using Bun's built-in test runner (`bun test`). This was created after a critical bug (`.includes()` vs `.startsWith()` in worktree filtering) that destroyed the project root via `rm -rf`.\n\n## Instructions\n\n- Use **only** Bun's built-in test runner (`bun test`) — no jest, vitest, or external test frameworks\n- Must cover worktree filtering edge cases (basename vs full-path matching — the bug that rm -rf'd the project)\n- Must cover arg parsing edge cases (trailing flags, missing values)\n- Must cover task YAML parsing (null, empty, invalid schema, invalid enums)\n- Use conventional commits: `feat(scope):`, `fix(scope):`, `refactor(scope):`, `docs(scope):`\n- Commit after each logical unit of work (roughly per subtask)\n- Do NOT push to remote — the orchestrator handles that\n- After completing all changes, run `bun run build` to verify everything works\n- The branch is `feature/unit-test-suite`, base is `main`\n\n## Discoveries\n\n1. **5 test files already existed** when we started, but 3 tests were failing due to the migration from single-file (`tasks.yml`) to folder-based task storage (`tasks/` directory with individual YAML files per task). The `loadFeatures()` function now delegates to `loadTasksFromStore()` which gracefully handles missing files and corrupted YAML (returns empty TasksFile instead of throwing), and subtasks are flattened into top-level tasks during migration.\n\n2. **Type mismatches existed in test helpers** — `makeConfig()` helpers across multiple test files were missing `tdd` and `cacheTTL` fields that were added to `WomboConfig`. `makeAgentState()` in state.test.ts was missing `schedule_plan`, `stream_index`, `depends_on`, `depended_on_by`, `agent_name`, `agent_type` fields.\n\n3. **`deepMerge` in config.ts is private** — can only be tested indirectly through `loadConfig()` by writing partial config.json files and verifying merge behavior.\n\n4. **`{ ...DEFAULT_CONFIG }` is a shallow copy** — tests that modify nested properties on a shallow copy corrupt shared references. Must use `JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(DEFAULT_CONFIG))` for deep copies in tests.\n\n5. **The task store uses folder-based storage** — tasks stored as individual YAML files in `.wombo-combo/tasks/` and `.wombo-combo/archive/` with `_meta.yml` for metadata. Legacy single-file format is auto-migrated, with subtasks flattened to top-level tasks with `depends_on` references.\n\n6. **tsconfig.json excludes tests/** from compilation — this is fine since Bun handles TypeScript natively for `bun test`.\n\n## Accomplished\n\n### Completed (all tests passing, all committed)\n\n1. **Fixed 3 failing tests in `features.test.ts`** (commit `cfef5a5`):\n   - Subtask normalization test updated to verify flattened form (subtasks become top-level tasks with `depends_on`)\n   - Corrupted YAML test now expects graceful degradation (empty TasksFile) instead of thrown error\n   - Missing file test now expects graceful degradation instead of thrown error\n   - Added missing `cacheTTL` and `tdd` fields to `makeConfig()`\n\n2. **Created `tests/task-schema.test.ts`** — 45 tests (commit `098b1da`):\n   - `validateTask`: valid tasks, missing required fields (id/title/status), invalid enum values for status/priority/difficulty, unparseable effort durations, completion out of range, depends_on type check, id format validation, null/empty input handling, multiple accumulated issues\n   - `validateMeta`: valid meta, missing version, missing/non-object meta block, missing inner fields, null input\n   - Enum arrays, ordering maps, field constants\n\n3. **Created `tests/validate.test.ts`** — 49 tests (commit `098b1da`):\n   - `validateId`: kebab-case, empty, uppercase, spaces, underscores, dots, path traversal, query params, fragments, percent-encoding, control chars, length limits, custom labels\n   - `validateText`: normal text, newlines/tabs, empty, unicode, control chars (null, bell, escape, DEL)\n   - `validateBranchName`: valid names, empty, double dots, spaces, special chars (~^:\\?*[), control chars\n   - `validateDuration`: ISO 8601 patterns, empty, plain numbers, human-readable, lowercase, missing P prefix\n   - `validateEnum`: allowed/disallowed values, empty, case sensitivity\n\n4. **Fixed type errors in existing test helpers** (commit `e2a5b52`):\n   - `tests/worktree.test.ts`: added `cacheTTL` and `tdd` to `makeConfig()`\n   - `tests/worktree-filtering.test.ts`: added `cacheTTL` and `tdd` to `makeConfig()`\n   - `tests/state.test.ts`: added `schedule_plan`, `stream_index`, `depends_on`, `depended_on_by`, `agent_name`, `agent_type` to `makeAgentState()` and `schedule_plan` to `makeWaveState()`\n\n5. **Created `tests/config.test.ts`** — 34 tests (commit `d7c1323`):\n   - `loadConfig`: defaults when no file, partial merge, deep merge of nested objects, array replacement, invalid JSON, legacy `tasksFile`/`archiveFile` migration, deep merge of `tdd` and `agentRegistry`\n   - `validateConfig`: all required fields, numeric constraints (`maxConcurrent`, `maxRetries`, `maxBackups`), enum validation (`agentRegistry.mode`), conditional validation (`tdd.testCommand` when enabled)\n   - `DEFAULT_CONFIG` and `generateDefaultConfig`\n\n6. **Created `tests/state-deps.test.ts`** — 30 tests (commit `d7c1323`):\n   - `areAgentDepsReady`: no deps, verified/merged/running/queued/completed/failed deps, external deps, multiple deps (all must be satisfied)\n   - `readyToLaunchAgents`: empty, queued no deps, excludes running/completed, excludes unsatisfied deps, multiple ready\n   - `getDownstreamAgents`: no downstream, direct, transitive, diamond dependencies, non-existent feature\n   - `cancelDownstream`: queued/running/